HEADWORD: Conventionalist
<hw>Con*ven"tion*al*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
adheres to a convention or treaty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is governed by conventionalism.</def>⟦br⟧
